id: decision-table
name: decision-table
title: Decision Table
version: 1.0.0
status: draft
domain: decision table
description: What recommendation-scoped triggers, local conditions, and actions form the decision logic?
derived_from:
  - korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
artifact_type: decision-table
clinical_question: What recommendation-scoped triggers, local conditions, and actions form the decision logic?
sections:
  summary: ASCO guidance organizes neoadjuvant therapy decisions around candidate selection, subtype-directed regimen planning, and treatment response monitoring for invasive nonmetastatic breast cancer.
  pathway_phases:
    - id: candidacy
      label: Candidacy and treatment intent
      description: Determine whether neoadjuvant systemic therapy is appropriate and what clinical goal it serves.
    - id: monitoring
      label: Response monitoring
      description: Monitor patients receiving neoadjuvant therapy and interpret treatment response.
    - id: tnbc
      label: Triple-negative breast cancer regimen selection
      description: Choose neoadjuvant treatment strategy for triple-negative breast cancer.
    - id: hr-her2-negative
      label: HR-positive HER2-negative regimen selection
      description: Choose chemotherapy or endocrine downstaging strategy for HR-positive HER2-negative disease.
    - id: her2-positive
      label: HER2-positive regimen selection
      description: Choose anti-HER2-based neoadjuvant treatment strategy.
  events:
    - id: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
      label: Assess neoadjuvant candidacy
      description: Initial multidisciplinary treatment planning for invasive nonmetastatic breast cancer.
      phase: candidacy
      trigger:
        type: named-event
        name: initial-breast-cancer-treatment-planning
        source: multidisciplinary-oncology-evaluation
    - id: monitor-neoadjuvant-response
      label: Monitor treatment response
      description: Ongoing assessment while the patient is receiving neoadjuvant therapy.
      phase: monitoring
      trigger:
        type: named-event
        name: active-neoadjuvant-treatment-course
        source: medical-oncology-follow-up
    - id: select-tnbc-regimen
      label: Select TNBC neoadjuvant regimen
      description: Choose neoadjuvant chemotherapy strategy for triple-negative breast cancer.
      phase: tnbc
      trigger:
        type: named-event
        name: tnbc-subtype-treatment-selection
+        source: subtype-directed-oncology-planning
    - id: select-hr-her2-negative-regimen
      label: Select HR-positive HER2-negative strategy
      description: Choose chemotherapy or endocrine downstaging approach for HR-positive HER2-negative disease.
      phase: hr-her2-negative
      trigger:
        type: named-event
        name: hr-positive-her2-negative-treatment-selection
        source: subtype-directed-oncology-planning
    - id: select-her2-positive-regimen
      label: Select HER2-positive neoadjuvant regimen
      description: Choose anti-HER2-based neoadjuvant therapy for HER2-positive disease.
      phase: her2-positive
      trigger:
        type: named-event
        name: her2-positive-treatment-selection
        source: subtype-directed-oncology-planning
  conditions:
    - id: inflammatory-or-locally-advanced
      label: Inflammatory or locally advanced unresectable disease
      description: Breast cancer is inflammatory, unresectable, or locally advanced and may become resectable with therapy.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: residual-disease-would-change-adjuvant-therapy
      label: Residual disease result would change adjuvant therapy
      description: Finding residual disease after neoadjuvant therapy would alter adjuvant treatment recommendations.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: local-therapy-downstaging-goal
      label: Downstaging or surgery extent reduction is a treatment goal
      description: Neoadjuvant therapy is being considered to reduce the extent of breast or axillary surgery.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: surgery-delay-context
      label: Surgery delay is preferable or unavoidable
      description: Surgery is delayed for decision-making, testing, or reconstructive planning.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: standard-tumor-features-available
      label: Histology grade stage and ER PR HER2 are available
      description: Standard clinicopathologic tumor features are available to guide neoadjuvant treatment selection.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: tnbc-node-positive-or-t1c-plus
      label: TNBC is node-positive or at least T1c
      description: Triple-negative breast cancer has clinically node-positive disease and-or tumor stage T1c or greater.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: tnbc-ct1ab-n0
      label: TNBC is cT1a or cT1b N0
      description: Triple-negative breast cancer is small and node-negative.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: benefit-harm-favors-carboplatin
      label: Benefit harm balance favors carboplatin
      description: The anticipated pathologic complete response benefit justifies carboplatin toxicity.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: hr-positive-her2-negative-disease
      label: HR-positive HER2-negative subtype
      description: Hormone receptor positive HER2-negative breast cancer subtype is confirmed.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: chemo-decision-without-surgical-data
      label: Chemotherapy decision can be made without surgical pathology or genomic testing
      description: Upfront surgical pathology or tumor-specific genomic testing is not required to decide on chemotherapy.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: postmenopausal
      label: Patient is postmenopausal
      description: Menopausal status supports neoadjuvant endocrine downstaging with an aromatase inhibitor.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: no-surgery-intended
      label: No surgery is intended
      description: Endocrine therapy is being used for disease control rather than bridge to surgery.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: premenopausal
      label: Patient is premenopausal
      description: Premenopausal status limits routine neoadjuvant endocrine therapy use outside trials.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: her2-positive-high-risk
      label: HER2-positive with node-positive or high-risk node-negative disease
      description: HER2-positive disease meets high-risk criteria for neoadjuvant systemic therapy.
      values: [Yes, No]
    - id: her2-t1ab-n0
      label: HER2-positive T1a or T1b N0 disease
      description: HER2-positive disease is small and node-negative.
      values: [Yes, No]
  data_elements:
    - id: de-inflammatory-stage
      condition_id: inflammatory-or-locally-advanced
      label: Clinical stage and resectability assessment
      description: Review inflammatory presentation, local extent, and initial surgical resectability.
      data_type: diagnosis
    - id: de-residual-disease-impact
      condition_id: residual-disease-would-change-adjuvant-therapy
      label: Potential adjuvant treatment change
      description: Determine whether residual disease findings would alter adjuvant treatment recommendations.
      data_type: assessment
    - id: de-local-therapy-goal
      condition_id: local-therapy-downstaging-goal
      label: Local therapy reduction goal
      description: Document whether the intent is to increase breast conservation or reduce axillary surgery.
      data_type: patient-reported
    - id: de-surgery-delay
      condition_id: surgery-delay-context
      label: Surgical timing constraints
      description: Document decision-making, testing, or reconstruction factors that justify delay in surgery.
      data_type: history
    - id: de-standard-features
      condition_id: standard-tumor-features-available
      label: Standard tumor biology features
      description: Review histology, grade, stage, estrogen receptor, progesterone receptor, and HER2 status.
      data_type: assessment
    - id: de-tnbc-stage
      condition_id: tnbc-node-positive-or-t1c-plus
      label: TNBC nodal and tumor stage
      description: Confirm node-positive status and whether disease is at least T1c.
      data_type: diagnosis
    - id: de-tnbc-small-node-negative
      condition_id: tnbc-ct1ab-n0
      label: Small node-negative TNBC status
      description: Confirm cT1a or cT1b N0 triple-negative breast cancer.
      data_type: diagnosis
    - id: de-carboplatin-risk-benefit
      condition_id: benefit-harm-favors-carboplatin
      label: Carboplatin risk benefit review
      description: Assess expected pCR benefit against toxicity and patient tolerance.
      data_type: assessment
    - id: de-hr-her2-subtype
      condition_id: hr-positive-her2-negative-disease
      label: HR-positive HER2-negative subtype confirmation
      description: Confirm hormone receptor positivity and HER2 negativity.
      data_type: diagnosis
    - id: de-chemo-decision-context
      condition_id: chemo-decision-without-surgical-data
      label: Need for surgical pathology or genomic data
      description: Determine whether chemotherapy selection can be made before surgery and genomic profiling.
      data_type: history
    - id: de-menopausal-status
      condition_id: postmenopausal
      label: Menopausal status
      description: Determine whether the patient is postmenopausal.
      data_type: history
    - id: de-surgery-intent
      condition_id: no-surgery-intended
      label: Surgical intent
      description: Determine whether surgery is planned after systemic therapy.
      data_type: history
    - id: de-premenopausal-status
      condition_id: premenopausal
      label: Premenopausal status
      description: Determine whether the patient is premenopausal.
      data_type: history
    - id: de-her2-risk
      condition_id: her2-positive-high-risk
      label: HER2-positive risk category
      description: Confirm node-positive disease or high-risk node-negative status in HER2-positive cancer.
      data_type: diagnosis
    - id: de-her2-small-node-negative
      condition_id: her2-t1ab-n0
      label: Small node-negative HER2-positive disease
      description: Confirm T1a or T1b N0 HER2-positive disease.
      data_type: diagnosis
  actions:
    - id: coordinate-multidisciplinary-management
      label: Coordinate multidisciplinary neoadjuvant management
      description: Manage the patient through a multidisciplinary care team while planning and delivering neoadjuvant therapy.
      kind: Task
      evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-general-team]
      provenance:
        source: source_direct
    - id: offer-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-for-advanced-disease
      label: Offer neoadjuvant chemotherapy for inflammatory or locally advanced disease
      description: Use neoadjuvant chemotherapy as the treatment of choice for inflammatory breast cancer or unresectable locally advanced disease that may become resectable.
      kind: MedicationRequest
      evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-1]
      provenance:
        source: source_direct
    - id: use-standard-tumor-features
      label: Use histology grade stage and receptor status to guide decisions
      description: Use tumor histology, grade, stage, and ER PR HER2 expression to guide the decision to pursue neoadjuvant chemotherapy.
      kind: Task
      evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-2]
      provenance:
        source: source_direct
    - id: avoid-other-markers
      label: Do not rely on other biomarkers or genomic profiles for neoadjuvant decision-making
      description: Do not use other immunochemical markers, morphologic markers, or genomic profiles to decide whether to pursue neoadjuvant chemotherapy.
      kind: Task
      do_not_perform: true
      evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-2]
      provenance:
        source: inferred
        rationale: The guideline states there is insufficient evidence to support routine use of these markers for this decision.
    - id: offer-neoadjuvant-for-residual-disease-guided-adjuvant-planning
      label: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy when residual disease will guide adjuvant planning
      description: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy to high-risk HER2-positive or triple-negative disease when residual disease findings will change adjuvant therapy.
      kind: ServiceRequest
      evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-3]
      provenance:
        source: source_direct
    - id: offer-neoadjuvant-for-downstaging
      label: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy to reduce surgery extent
      description: Use chemotherapy with or without targeted therapy, or endocrine therapy when HR-positive, to reduce the extent of local therapy.
      kind: ServiceRequest
      evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-4]
      provenance:
        source: source_direct
    - id: offer-neoadjuvant-for-surgery-delay
      label: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy when surgery is delayed
      description: Use neoadjuvant systemic therapy when delaying surgery is preferable or unavoidable.
      kind: ServiceRequest
      evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-5]
      provenance:
        source: source_direct
    - id: monitor-with-clinical-examination

