+    - claim_id: claim-general-team
+      statement: Patients undergoing neoadjuvant therapy should be managed by a multidisciplinary care team.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: Recommendations summary paragraph before Clinical Question 1
+    - claim_id: claim-r1-1
+      statement: Neoadjuvant chemotherapy is the treatment of choice for inflammatory breast cancer or unresectable locally advanced disease that may become resectable.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.1
+    - claim_id: claim-r1-2
+      statement: Tumor histology, grade, stage, and ER PR HER2 expression should guide neoadjuvant decisions; other markers and genomic profiles should not.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.2
+    - claim_id: claim-r1-3
+      statement: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy to high-risk HER2-positive or triple-negative disease when residual disease would guide adjuvant treatment recommendations.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.3
+    - claim_id: claim-r1-4
+      statement: Neoadjuvant systemic therapy may be used to reduce the extent of surgery, including increasing breast-conserving options.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.4
+    - claim_id: claim-r1-5
+      statement: Neoadjuvant systemic therapy may be offered when surgery is delayed for testing, reconstruction planning, or other decision-making needs.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.5
+    - claim_id: claim-r2-1
+      statement: Monitor response with regular clinical examination and use the most informative baseline imaging modality when imaging is needed.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 2.1
+    - claim_id: claim-r2-2
+      statement: Blood-based and tissue-based biomarkers should not be used to monitor response during neoadjuvant therapy.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 2.2
+    - claim_id: claim-r2-3
+      statement: Pathologic complete response should be used to guide clinical decision making after neoadjuvant therapy.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 2.3
+    - claim_id: claim-r3-1
+      statement: Offer anthracycline- and taxane-containing neoadjuvant therapy for TNBC with node-positive disease or at least T1c disease.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.1
+    - claim_id: claim-r3-2
+      statement: Do not routinely offer neoadjuvant therapy for cT1a or cT1b N0 TNBC outside a clinical trial.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.2
+    - claim_id: claim-r3-3
+      statement: Carboplatin may be offered in TNBC to increase the likelihood of pathologic complete response after balancing benefits and harms.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.3
+    - claim_id: claim-r3-4
+      statement: There is insufficient evidence to recommend routinely adding immune checkpoint inhibitors to neoadjuvant chemotherapy in early-stage TNBC.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.4
+    - claim_id: claim-r4-1
+      statement: Neoadjuvant chemotherapy can be used in HR-positive HER2-negative disease when the chemotherapy decision can be made without surgical pathology or genomic testing.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 4.1
+    - claim_id: claim-r4-2
+      statement: In postmenopausal HR-positive HER2-negative disease, neoadjuvant endocrine therapy with an aromatase inhibitor may increase locoregional treatment options, and endocrine therapy may be used for disease control if surgery is not intended.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 4.2
+    - claim_id: claim-r4-3
+      statement: Premenopausal patients with HR-positive HER2-negative early-stage disease should not routinely receive neoadjuvant endocrine therapy outside a clinical trial.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 4.3
+    - claim_id: claim-r5-1
+      statement: Offer trastuzumab-based neoadjuvant therapy for node-positive or high-risk node-negative HER2-positive disease, and pertuzumab may be added with trastuzumab.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 5.1
+    - claim_id: claim-r5-2
+      statement: Do not routinely offer neoadjuvant chemotherapy or anti-HER2 agents for T1a N0 or T1b N0 HER2-positive disease outside a clinical trial.
+      evidence:
+        - source: korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
+          locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 5.2
