 succeeded in 0ms:
id: decision-table
name: decision-table
title: Decision Table
version: 1.0.0
status: draft
domain: decision table
description: What recommendation-scoped triggers, local conditions, and actions 
  form the decision logic?
derived_from:
- korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
artifact_type: decision-table
clinical_question: What recommendation-scoped triggers, local conditions, and 
  actions form the decision logic?
sections:
  summary: ASCO guidance organizes neoadjuvant therapy decisions around 
    candidate selection, subtype-directed regimen planning, and treatment 
    response monitoring for invasive nonmetastatic breast cancer.
  pathway_phases:
  - id: candidacy
    label: Candidacy and treatment intent
    description: Determine whether neoadjuvant systemic therapy is appropriate 
      and what clinical goal it serves.
  - id: monitoring
    label: Response monitoring
    description: Monitor patients receiving neoadjuvant therapy and interpret 
      treatment response.
  - id: tnbc
    label: Triple-negative breast cancer regimen selection
    description: Choose neoadjuvant treatment strategy for triple-negative 
      breast cancer.
  - id: hr-her2-negative
    label: HR-positive HER2-negative regimen selection
    description: Choose chemotherapy or endocrine downstaging strategy for 
      HR-positive HER2-negative disease.
  - id: her2-positive
    label: HER2-positive regimen selection
    description: Choose anti-HER2-based neoadjuvant treatment strategy.
  events:
  - id: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
    label: Assess neoadjuvant candidacy
    description: Initial multidisciplinary treatment planning for invasive 
      nonmetastatic breast cancer.
    phase: candidacy
    trigger:
      type: named-event
      name: initial-breast-cancer-treatment-planning
      source: multidisciplinary-oncology-evaluation
  - id: monitor-neoadjuvant-response
    label: Monitor treatment response
    description: Ongoing assessment while the patient is receiving neoadjuvant 
      therapy.
    phase: monitoring
    trigger:
      type: named-event
      name: active-neoadjuvant-treatment-course
      source: medical-oncology-follow-up
  - id: select-tnbc-regimen
    label: Select TNBC neoadjuvant regimen
    description: Choose neoadjuvant chemotherapy strategy for triple-negative 
      breast cancer.
    phase: tnbc
    trigger:
      type: named-event
      name: tnbc-subtype-treatment-selection
      source: subtype-directed-oncology-planning
  - id: select-hr-her2-negative-regimen
    label: Select HR-positive HER2-negative strategy
    description: Choose chemotherapy or endocrine downstaging approach for 
      HR-positive HER2-negative disease.
    phase: hr-her2-negative
    trigger:
      type: named-event
      name: hr-positive-her2-negative-treatment-selection
      source: subtype-directed-oncology-planning
  - id: select-her2-positive-regimen
    label: Select HER2-positive neoadjuvant regimen
    description: Choose anti-HER2-based neoadjuvant therapy for HER2-positive 
      disease.
    phase: her2-positive
    trigger:
      type: named-event
      name: her2-positive-treatment-selection
      source: subtype-directed-oncology-planning
  conditions:
  - id: inflammatory-or-locally-advanced
    label: Inflammatory or locally advanced unresectable disease
    description: Breast cancer is inflammatory, unresectable, or locally 
      advanced and may become resectable with therapy.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: residual-disease-would-change-adjuvant-therapy
    label: Residual disease result would change adjuvant therapy
    description: Finding residual disease after neoadjuvant therapy would alter 
      adjuvant treatment recommendations.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: local-therapy-downstaging-goal
    label: Downstaging or surgery extent reduction is a treatment goal
    description: Neoadjuvant therapy is being considered to reduce the extent of
      breast or axillary surgery.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: surgery-delay-context
    label: Surgery delay is preferable or unavoidable
    description: Surgery is delayed for decision-making, testing, or 
      reconstructive planning.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: standard-tumor-features-available
    label: Histology grade stage and ER PR HER2 are available
    description: Standard clinicopathologic tumor features are available to 
      guide neoadjuvant treatment selection.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: tnbc-node-positive-or-t1c-plus
    label: TNBC is node-positive or at least T1c
    description: Triple-negative breast cancer has clinically node-positive 
      disease and-or tumor stage T1c or greater.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: tnbc-ct1ab-n0
    label: TNBC is cT1a or cT1b N0
    description: Triple-negative breast cancer is small and node-negative.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: benefit-harm-favors-carboplatin
    label: Benefit harm balance favors carboplatin
    description: The anticipated pathologic complete response benefit justifies 
      carboplatin toxicity.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: hr-positive-her2-negative-disease
    label: HR-positive HER2-negative subtype
    description: Hormone receptor positive HER2-negative breast cancer subtype 
      is confirmed.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: chemo-decision-without-surgical-data
    label: Chemotherapy decision can be made without surgical pathology or 
      genomic testing
    description: Upfront surgical pathology or tumor-specific genomic testing is
      not required to decide on chemotherapy.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: postmenopausal
    label: Patient is postmenopausal
    description: Menopausal status supports neoadjuvant endocrine downstaging 
      with an aromatase inhibitor.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: no-surgery-intended
    label: No surgery is intended
    description: Endocrine therapy is being used for disease control rather than
      bridge to surgery.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: premenopausal
    label: Patient is premenopausal
    description: Premenopausal status limits routine neoadjuvant endocrine 
      therapy use outside trials.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: her2-positive-high-risk
    label: HER2-positive with node-positive or high-risk node-negative disease
    description: HER2-positive disease meets high-risk criteria for neoadjuvant 
      systemic therapy.
    values: [Yes, No]
  - id: her2-t1ab-n0
    label: HER2-positive T1a or T1b N0 disease
    description: HER2-positive disease is small and node-negative.
    values: [Yes, No]
  data_elements:
  - id: de-inflammatory-stage
    condition_id: inflammatory-or-locally-advanced
    label: Clinical stage and resectability assessment
    description: Review inflammatory presentation, local extent, and initial 
      surgical resectability.
    data_type: diagnosis
  - id: de-residual-disease-impact
    condition_id: residual-disease-would-change-adjuvant-therapy
    label: Potential adjuvant treatment change
    description: Determine whether residual disease findings would alter 
      adjuvant treatment recommendations.
    data_type: assessment
  - id: de-local-therapy-goal
    condition_id: local-therapy-downstaging-goal
    label: Local therapy reduction goal
    description: Document whether the intent is to increase breast conservation 
      or reduce axillary surgery.
    data_type: patient-reported
  - id: de-surgery-delay
    condition_id: surgery-delay-context
    label: Surgical timing constraints
    description: Document decision-making, testing, or reconstruction factors 
      that justify delay in surgery.
    data_type: history
  - id: de-standard-features
    condition_id: standard-tumor-features-available
    label: Standard tumor biology features
    description: Review histology, grade, stage, estrogen receptor, progesterone
      receptor, and HER2 status.
    data_type: assessment
  - id: de-tnbc-stage
    condition_id: tnbc-node-positive-or-t1c-plus
    label: TNBC nodal and tumor stage
    description: Confirm node-positive status and whether disease is at least 
      T1c.
    data_type: diagnosis
  - id: de-tnbc-small-node-negative
    condition_id: tnbc-ct1ab-n0
    label: Small node-negative TNBC status
    description: Confirm cT1a or cT1b N0 triple-negative breast cancer.
    data_type: diagnosis
  - id: de-carboplatin-risk-benefit
    condition_id: benefit-harm-favors-carboplatin
    label: Carboplatin risk benefit review
    description: Assess expected pCR benefit against toxicity and patient 
      tolerance.
    data_type: assessment
  - id: de-hr-her2-subtype
    condition_id: hr-positive-her2-negative-disease
    label: HR-positive HER2-negative subtype confirmation
    description: Confirm hormone receptor positivity and HER2 negativity.
    data_type: diagnosis
  - id: de-chemo-decision-context
    condition_id: chemo-decision-without-surgical-data
    label: Need for surgical pathology or genomic data
    description: Determine whether chemotherapy selection can be made before 
      surgery and genomic profiling.
    data_type: history
  - id: de-menopausal-status
    condition_id: postmenopausal
    label: Menopausal status
    description: Determine whether the patient is postmenopausal.
    data_type: history
  - id: de-surgery-intent
    condition_id: no-surgery-intended
    label: Surgical intent
    description: Determine whether surgery is planned after systemic therapy.
    data_type: history
  - id: de-premenopausal-status
    condition_id: premenopausal
    label: Premenopausal status
    description: Determine whether the patient is premenopausal.
    data_type: history
  - id: de-her2-risk
    condition_id: her2-positive-high-risk
    label: HER2-positive risk category
    description: Confirm node-positive disease or high-risk node-negative status
      in HER2-positive cancer.
    data_type: diagnosis
  - id: de-her2-small-node-negative
    condition_id: her2-t1ab-n0
    label: Small node-negative HER2-positive disease
    description: Confirm T1a or T1b N0 HER2-positive disease.
    data_type: diagnosis
  actions:
  - id: coordinate-multidisciplinary-management
    label: Coordinate multidisciplinary neoadjuvant management
    description: Manage the patient through a multidisciplinary care team while 
      planning and delivering neoadjuvant therapy.
    kind: Task
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-general-team]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: offer-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-for-advanced-disease
    label: Offer neoadjuvant chemotherapy for inflammatory or locally advanced 
      disease
    description: Use neoadjuvant chemotherapy as the treatment of choice for 
      inflammatory breast cancer or unresectable locally advanced disease that 
      may become resectable.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: use-standard-tumor-features
    label: Use histology grade stage and receptor status to guide decisions
    description: Use tumor histology, grade, stage, and ER PR HER2 expression to
      guide the decision to pursue neoadjuvant chemotherapy.
    kind: Task
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: avoid-other-markers
    label: Do not rely on other biomarkers or genomic profiles for neoadjuvant 
      decision-making
    description: Do not use other immunochemical markers, morphologic markers, 
      or genomic profiles to decide whether to pursue neoadjuvant chemotherapy.
    kind: Task
    do_not_perform: true
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-2]
    provenance:
      source: inferred
      rationale: The guideline states there is insufficient evidence to support 
        routine use of these markers for this decision.
  - id: offer-neoadjuvant-for-residual-disease-guided-adjuvant-planning
    label: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy when residual disease will guide 
      adjuvant planning
    description: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy to high-risk HER2-positive 
      or triple-negative disease when residual disease findings will change 
      adjuvant therapy.
    kind: ServiceRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-3]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: offer-neoadjuvant-for-downstaging
    label: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy to reduce surgery extent
    description: Use chemotherapy with or without targeted therapy, or endocrine
      therapy when HR-positive, to reduce the extent of local therapy.
    kind: ServiceRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-4]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: offer-neoadjuvant-for-surgery-delay
    label: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy when surgery is delayed
    description: Use neoadjuvant systemic therapy when delaying surgery is 
      preferable or unavoidable.
    kind: ServiceRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-5]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: monitor-with-clinical-examination
    label: Monitor response with regular clinical examination
    description: Use regular clinical examination to monitor patients receiving 
      neoadjuvant therapy.
    kind: Task
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r2-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: use-baseline-informative-imaging
    label: Use the most informative baseline imaging modality when imaging is 
      needed
    description: Use mammography, ultrasound, or MRI that was most informative 
      at baseline to confirm progression or support surgical planning.
    kind: ServiceRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r2-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: avoid-blood-and-tissue-biomarker-monitoring
    label: Do not use blood or tissue biomarkers for monitoring
    description: Do not use blood-based or tissue-based biomarkers to monitor 
      patients receiving neoadjuvant therapy.
    kind: Task
    do_not_perform: true
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r2-2]
    provenance:
      source: inferred
      rationale: The guideline directly recommends against using biomarkers for 
        treatment monitoring.
  - id: use-pcr-to-guide-decisions
    label: Use pathologic complete response to guide decision-making
    description: Use pathologic complete response, defined as absence of 
      invasive disease in breast and lymph nodes, to guide clinical 
      decision-making.
    kind: Task
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r2-3]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: offer-anthracycline-taxane-for-tnbc
    label: Offer anthracycline and taxane regimen for eligible TNBC
    description: Offer an anthracycline-containing and taxane-containing 
      neoadjuvant regimen for TNBC with clinically node-positive disease and-or 
      at least T1c disease.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: avoid-neoadjuvant-therapy-for-small-tnbc
    label: Do not routinely offer neoadjuvant therapy for cT1a or cT1b N0 TNBC
    description: Avoid routine neoadjuvant therapy outside a clinical trial for 
      small node-negative TNBC.
    kind: ServiceRequest
    do_not_perform: true
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-2]
    provenance:
      source: inferred
      rationale: The recommendation explicitly states these patients should not 
        routinely receive neoadjuvant therapy outside trials.
  - id: consider-carboplatin-for-tnbc
    label: Consider carboplatin to increase pathologic complete response
    description: Carboplatin may be added as part of a neoadjuvant TNBC regimen 
      after weighing potential benefits and harms.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-3]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: avoid-routine-immune-checkpoint-inhibitors
    label: Do not routinely add immune checkpoint inhibitors to neoadjuvant 
      chemotherapy
    description: Do not routinely add immune checkpoint inhibitors to standard 
      neoadjuvant chemotherapy for early-stage TNBC.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    do_not_perform: true
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-4]
    provenance:
      source: inferred
      rationale: The guideline states evidence is insufficient to recommend 
        routine addition of immune checkpoint inhibitors.
  - id: use-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-without-surgical-data
    label: Use neoadjuvant chemotherapy when the chemotherapy decision does not 
      require surgical data
    description: Neoadjuvant chemotherapy can substitute for adjuvant 
      chemotherapy in HR-positive HER2-negative disease when surgical pathology 
      or genomic testing is not required for the decision.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: offer-postmenopausal-neoadjuvant-endocrine-therapy
    label: Offer aromatase inhibitor based neoadjuvant endocrine therapy for 
      postmenopausal downstaging
    description: Use neoadjuvant endocrine therapy with an aromatase inhibitor 
      in postmenopausal HR-positive HER2-negative disease to increase 
      locoregional treatment options.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: use-endocrine-therapy-for-disease-control
    label: Use endocrine therapy for disease control when surgery is not planned
    description: Use endocrine therapy for disease control if there is no intent
      to proceed to surgery.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: avoid-premenopausal-neoadjuvant-endocrine-therapy
    label: Do not routinely offer neoadjuvant endocrine therapy to premenopausal
      patients
    description: Avoid routine neoadjuvant endocrine therapy outside a clinical 
      trial in premenopausal HR-positive HER2-negative early-stage disease.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    do_not_perform: true
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-3]
    provenance:
      source: inferred
      rationale: The recommendation restricts routine premenopausal neoadjuvant 
        endocrine therapy to clinical trials.
  - id: offer-her2-directed-neoadjuvant-regimen
    label: Offer trastuzumab-based neoadjuvant therapy for high-risk 
      HER2-positive disease
    description: Offer anthracycline and taxane or non-anthracycline regimen in 
      combination with trastuzumab for node-positive or high-risk node-negative 
      HER2-positive disease.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r5-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: consider-pertuzumab-with-trastuzumab
    label: Consider pertuzumab with trastuzumab
    description: Pertuzumab may be used with trastuzumab in the neoadjuvant 
      setting for HER2-positive disease.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r5-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: avoid-neoadjuvant-therapy-for-small-her2-positive
    label: Do not routinely offer neoadjuvant chemotherapy or anti-HER2 therapy 
      for T1a or T1b N0 HER2-positive disease
    description: Avoid routine neoadjuvant chemotherapy or anti-HER2 agents 
      outside a clinical trial for small node-negative HER2-positive disease.
    kind: MedicationRequest
    do_not_perform: true
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r5-2]
    provenance:
      source: inferred
      rationale: The recommendation explicitly advises against routine 
        neoadjuvant treatment in this low-stage subgroup outside trials.
  rules:
  - id: rule-multidisciplinary-management
    event: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
    phase: candidacy
    then:
    - coordinate-multidisciplinary-management
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-general-team]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r1-1-advanced-disease
    event: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
    phase: candidacy
    when:
      inflammatory-or-locally-advanced: Yes
    then:
    - offer-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-for-advanced-disease
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r1-2-standard-features
    event: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
    phase: candidacy
    when:
      standard-tumor-features-available: Yes
    then:
    - use-standard-tumor-features
    - avoid-other-markers
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r1-3-residual-disease-guided
    event: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
    phase: candidacy
    when:
      residual-disease-would-change-adjuvant-therapy: Yes
    then:
    - offer-neoadjuvant-for-residual-disease-guided-adjuvant-planning
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-3]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r1-4-downstaging
    event: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
    phase: candidacy
    when:
      local-therapy-downstaging-goal: Yes
    then:
    - offer-neoadjuvant-for-downstaging
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-4]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r1-5-surgery-delay
    event: assess-neoadjuvant-candidacy
    phase: candidacy
    when:
      surgery-delay-context: Yes
    then:
    - offer-neoadjuvant-for-surgery-delay
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r1-5]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r2-1-monitoring
    event: monitor-neoadjuvant-response
    phase: monitoring
    then:
    - monitor-with-clinical-examination
    - use-baseline-informative-imaging
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r2-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r2-2-no-biomarkers
    event: monitor-neoadjuvant-response
    phase: monitoring
    then:
    - avoid-blood-and-tissue-biomarker-monitoring
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r2-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r2-3-use-pcr
    event: monitor-neoadjuvant-response
    phase: monitoring
    then:
    - use-pcr-to-guide-decisions
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r2-3]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r3-1-tnbc-eligible
    event: select-tnbc-regimen
    phase: tnbc
    when:
      tnbc-node-positive-or-t1c-plus: Yes
    then:
    - offer-anthracycline-taxane-for-tnbc
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r3-2-tnbc-small-node-negative
    event: select-tnbc-regimen
    phase: tnbc
    when:
      tnbc-ct1ab-n0: Yes
    then:
    - avoid-neoadjuvant-therapy-for-small-tnbc
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r3-3-carboplatin
    event: select-tnbc-regimen
    phase: tnbc
    when:
      tnbc-node-positive-or-t1c-plus: Yes
      benefit-harm-favors-carboplatin: Yes
    then:
    - consider-carboplatin-for-tnbc
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-3]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r3-4-no-ici
    event: select-tnbc-regimen
    phase: tnbc
    then:
    - avoid-routine-immune-checkpoint-inhibitors
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r3-4]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r4-1-use-chemo
    event: select-hr-her2-negative-regimen
    phase: hr-her2-negative
    when:
      hr-positive-her2-negative-disease: Yes
      chemo-decision-without-surgical-data: Yes
    then:
    - use-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-without-surgical-data
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r4-2-postmenopausal-endocrine
    event: select-hr-her2-negative-regimen
    phase: hr-her2-negative
    when:
      hr-positive-her2-negative-disease: Yes
      postmenopausal: Yes
    then:
    - offer-postmenopausal-neoadjuvant-endocrine-therapy
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r4-2-no-surgery
    event: select-hr-her2-negative-regimen
    phase: hr-her2-negative
    when:
      hr-positive-her2-negative-disease: Yes
      no-surgery-intended: Yes
    then:
    - use-endocrine-therapy-for-disease-control
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r4-3-premenopausal
    event: select-hr-her2-negative-regimen
    phase: hr-her2-negative
    when:
      hr-positive-her2-negative-disease: Yes
      premenopausal: Yes
    then:
    - avoid-premenopausal-neoadjuvant-endocrine-therapy
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r4-3]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r5-1-her2-high-risk
    event: select-her2-positive-regimen
    phase: her2-positive
    when:
      her2-positive-high-risk: Yes
    then:
    - offer-her2-directed-neoadjuvant-regimen
    - consider-pertuzumab-with-trastuzumab
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r5-1]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  - id: rule-r5-2-small-her2-positive
    event: select-her2-positive-regimen
    phase: her2-positive
    when:
      her2-t1ab-n0: Yes
    then:
    - avoid-neoadjuvant-therapy-for-small-her2-positive
    evidence_traceability_ids: [claim-r5-2]
    provenance:
      source: source_direct
  evidence_traceability:
  - claim_id: claim-general-team
    statement: Patients undergoing neoadjuvant therapy should be managed by a 
      multidisciplinary care team.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: Recommendations summary paragraph before Clinical Question 1
  - claim_id: claim-r1-1
    statement: Neoadjuvant chemotherapy is the treatment of choice for 
      inflammatory breast cancer or unresectable locally advanced disease that 
      may become resectable.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.1
  - claim_id: claim-r1-2
    statement: Tumor histology, grade, stage, and ER PR HER2 expression should 
      guide neoadjuvant decisions; other markers and genomic profiles should 
      not.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.2
  - claim_id: claim-r1-3
    statement: Offer neoadjuvant systemic therapy to high-risk HER2-positive or 
      triple-negative disease when residual disease would guide adjuvant 
      treatment recommendations.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.3
  - claim_id: claim-r1-4
    statement: Neoadjuvant systemic therapy may be used to reduce the extent of 
      surgery, including increasing breast-conserving options.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.4
  - claim_id: claim-r1-5
    statement: Neoadjuvant systemic therapy may be offered when surgery is 
      delayed for testing, reconstruction planning, or other decision-making 
      needs.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 1.5
  - claim_id: claim-r2-1
    statement: Monitor response with regular clinical examination and use the 
      most informative baseline imaging modality when imaging is needed.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 2.1
  - claim_id: claim-r2-2
    statement: Blood-based and tissue-based biomarkers should not be used to 
      monitor response during neoadjuvant therapy.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 2.2
  - claim_id: claim-r2-3
    statement: Pathologic complete response should be used to guide clinical 
      decision making after neoadjuvant therapy.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 2.3
  - claim_id: claim-r3-1
    statement: Offer anthracycline- and taxane-containing neoadjuvant therapy 
      for TNBC with node-positive disease or at least T1c disease.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.1
  - claim_id: claim-r3-2
    statement: Do not routinely offer neoadjuvant therapy for cT1a or cT1b N0 
      TNBC outside a clinical trial.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.2
  - claim_id: claim-r3-3
    statement: Carboplatin may be offered in TNBC to increase the likelihood of 
      pathologic complete response after balancing benefits and harms.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.3
  - claim_id: claim-r3-4
    statement: There is insufficient evidence to recommend routinely adding 
      immune checkpoint inhibitors to neoadjuvant chemotherapy in early-stage 
      TNBC.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 3.4
  - claim_id: claim-r4-1
    statement: Neoadjuvant chemotherapy can be used in HR-positive HER2-negative
      disease when the chemotherapy decision can be made without surgical 
      pathology or genomic testing.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 4.1
  - claim_id: claim-r4-2
    statement: In postmenopausal HR-positive HER2-negative disease, neoadjuvant 
      endocrine therapy with an aromatase inhibitor may increase locoregional 
      treatment options, and endocrine therapy may be used for disease control 
      if surgery is not intended.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 4.2
  - claim_id: claim-r4-3
    statement: Premenopausal patients with HR-positive HER2-negative early-stage
      disease should not routinely receive neoadjuvant endocrine therapy outside
      a clinical trial.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 4.3
  - claim_id: claim-r5-1
    statement: Offer trastuzumab-based neoadjuvant therapy for node-positive or 
      high-risk node-negative HER2-positive disease, and pertuzumab may be added
      with trastuzumab.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 5.1
  - claim_id: claim-r5-2
    statement: Do not routinely offer neoadjuvant chemotherapy or anti-HER2 
      agents for T1a N0 or T1b N0 HER2-positive disease outside a clinical 
      trial.
    evidence:
    - source: 
        korde-et-al-2021-neoadjuvant-chemotherapy-endocrine-therapy-and-targeted-therapy-for-breast-cancer-asco-guideline_pdf
      locator: The Bottom Line, Recommendation 5.2
