codex
Completed the full lifecycle for `asco-breast-cancer-guideline` through L3 computable artifacts. The topic is now at `l3-computable` in `rh-skills status show`.

I ingested and annotated the ASCO source, ran extract planning, completed concept enrichment/review, approved all artifacts, and ensured both a decision table and care pathway were derived. The key L2 outputs are [decision-table.yaml](/Users/taylorkingston/rh-skills-projects/asco-cancer-guideline/topics/asco-breast-cancer-guideline/structured/decision-table/decision-table.yaml), [care-pathway.yaml](/Users/taylorkingston/rh-skills-projects/asco-cancer-guideline/topics/asco-breast-cancer-guideline/structured/care-pathway/care-pathway.yaml), and [concepts.yaml](/Users/taylorkingston/rh-skills-projects/asco-cancer-guideline/topics/asco-breast-cancer-guideline/structured/concepts/concepts.yaml). The planner initially omitted `care-pathway`, so I added it to the extract control plan before approval to satisfy your requirement and keep sequencing separate from recommendation logic.

For formalization, I initialized [formalize-config.yaml](/Users/taylorkingston/rh-skills-projects/asco-cancer-guideline/topics/asco-breast-cancer-guideline/process/formalize-config.yaml), formalized terminology, pathway, and decision-table resources, authored and validated [AscoBreastCancerGuidelineRecommendationLogic.cql](/Users/taylorkingston/rh-skills-projects/asco-cancer-guideline/topics/asco-breast-cancer-guideline/computable/AscoBreastCancerGuidelineRecommendationLogic.cql), translated it to ELM, re-embedded the CQL into the Library JSON, resolved the remaining `TODO:MCP-UNREACHABLE` action codes, and rebuilt the package. The translated ELM JSON was moved to [AscoBreastCancerGuidelineRecommendationLogic.elm.json](/Users/taylorkingston/rh-skills-projects/asco-cancer-guideline/topics/asco-breast-cancer-guideline/process/elm/AscoBreastCancerGuidelineRecommendationLogic.elm.json) so L3 FHIR validation would pass cleanly.

Verification completed successfully:
- `rh-skills ingest verify asco-breast-cancer-guideline`
- `rh-skills cql validate asco-breast-cancer-guideline AscoBreastCancerGuidelineRecommendationLogic`
